{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"zippy-trapezial-buzzard","description":"## What\n\nOnce the generated CLI and MCP references exist, trim the duplicated, volatile\ncommand/tool/config catalogs out of `README.md` and replace them with links to the\ngenerated references. Keep the README focused on what rebar is, install, the tested\nquickstart, and routing links. This reduces the README's maintenance surface without\ngutting the front door.\n\nSequenced AFTER the CLI/MCP reference generators land (this ticket `depends_on` them)\nso the README points at real generated pages rather than removing content with no\nreplacement.\n\n## Scope\n- Identify command/tool/config catalogs in `README.md` now covered by generated\n  references and replace them with a short pointer + link.\n- Preserve the narrative front-door content (what/why, install, tested quickstart,\n  routing).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Volatile catalogs duplicated from the generated references are removed from\n      `README.md` and replaced with links.\n- [ ] The README still stands alone as an intro (what/install/quickstart/routing).\n- [ ] No dead links (passes the docs link/index CI gate).\n\nFiles: `README.md`.","id":"b5a4-e065-a252-4bc5","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":3,"tags":["docs","p2"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P2: Trim duplicated command/config catalogs from README (after generated refs)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814585625119001,"uuid":"73315f00-6165-4796-bd9b-8cf7717e7970"}